      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a revised version with a more personal touch:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We were truly impressed by your technical skills and experience, and your interview with our team was one of the highlights of our process. Your passion for coding and your collaborative spirit really stood out to us, and we appreciated the time you took to talk with us about your vision for our team.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills and fit are slightly better aligned with our current needs. Please know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely torn between the two of you. Your talent and enthusiasm made it a tough choice for our panel, and we have no doubt that you will find a great opportunity that matches your skills.\n\nWe want to emphasize that this decision is in no way a reflection on your abilities or potential as a developer. You would have been an excellent addition to our team, and we wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors.\n\nThank you again for your interest in joining our team, and we wish you all the best.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nThis",
